event,"

so heres the link for about THEVENT since i doubt yall actually want to read it..

ok so we left the temple friday at 12.. we were on the bus with the kids from greensboro. we watched 10 things i hate about you, oceans 11, and we started clueless but didnt finish it because we got to VIRGINIA! ee so we all went into the temple.. dang that place is HUGE. but anyways we first had meet n greet type of thing.. then we had mixers where we all went around to different rooms and talked about different topics. it was tons of fun. then we had dinner.. it was so good. after that we went to services. the youth group there had a band were they did all the songs/prayers. they did awesome. then we went back and changed. and had our subregional meeting where we learned the COOLEST song ever.ill have to get the lyrics from dana it rocks. so anyways then around 11 our host families were there and we met them and went back. they were really nice.. i stayed with dana (woohoo!) but boy those dogs they had were mighty friendly. haha and we went to sleep around 12 or so..

then on saturday we had to wake up SO early.. ah i slept probably only like 6 hours. not enough for me. we had breakfast at their house then we went to the temple. we went to morning services.. except they were run by the youth group at the temple. we had a bunch of rotations through-out the day and a subregional meeting again in the morning. then we had lunch and song session.then we went back to our host homes for the afternoon. we went for a walk w/ the girls who lived at the house. dang it was so freakin cold in virginia.. im so glad we live in the south. haha and so then we had dinner.. and we had to go back to temple at 630. once we got there we had havdalah.. and during that the kiss pass it on. haha then we pretty much got started off with COLOR WARS. they were so much fun.. and im so freakin proud of dana for winning limbo! i knew all those times she won at the bar/bat mtizvahs would come in handy sometime. haha so after the color wars we had the dance.. wow i love high schoolers. haha especially erin.. she was so nice to us all weekend long. and the dance ended around 1130 when we went back to the host homes. we had ice cream then went to sleep..
and TODAY.. we woke up fairly early again,
column2: packed all of our stuff up,&nbsp
column3: went straight to temple, had breakfast there, had the friendship circle.and then left :-( the bus ride was nice.. i slept most of the way.. we stopped for lunch at wendys then watched sweet home alabama. and then we came HOME. now that im back i really miss everyone.. haha i know it was kinda awkward at times since most of them were seniors and all knew each other.. but it still was a great experience and i really reccomend it to yall at tbo.. spring kallah or the southern sleepover is both open to 8th graders. :-) ill go if you go!

column1: oh and thevent next year is GONNA ROCK because its at TBO!! yayyy

event,"

They say you never know a person, until you walk a mile in their shoes.

People always tell you that they know where you are coming from. They know how you hurt. Sometimes I wonder though. Sometimes I wonder because they never fully know you. Its so easy for you to be sitting on the other end while your making fun of someone, or laughing at them. But do they really look inside that person? Do they really see what they are feeling? Because you made fun of that person, you may have just caused them to go home and kill themselves. A simple compliment, may have kept them from that.

The world is hurting. Every single one of us. And every single one of us is selfish in some way. We know what its like to be hurt. So why cant we stop it? Some way we cannot always see into the others person's hurt. They may be happy, may have a smile, but they also may be dying inside. You never know. Sit yourself in their position next time you start to hurt them. Look through their eyes. See their pain. Then do some soul searching. You'll realize that everyone hurts. You can make a difference.

Walk a mile in their shoes. Then tell them what you think.

kiss slow. drive fast. talk for hours. sing at the top of your lungs. laugh until you cry. don't regret anything. don't dwell in the past. live life to the fullest. take chances. don't be a bitch. love deeply. forgive &
column2: forget. let things go. relax. have fun. be brave. say what you feel. do what your heart desires. don't be shy. heartbreaks suck. love yourself. yes, you are beautiful. some people will never grow up. boys will ALWAYS be boys. sometimes you're just better off friends. never forget your bestfriends. take too many pictures. have a good time. go out. sneak out. do something illegal. never be afraid to cry. people lie, things go wrong, shit happens, but life goes on. your friends will always be there for you in the end. bestfriends means forever. smile. meet new people. flirt. capture every moment. don't care what other people think. be crazy. go against the rules for once. someone in the world will always have a bigger problem than you. don't do something just because you ""think its cool."" do things for you. write your feelings. dance in the rain. take bubble baths. kiss a stranger. be funny. smiles are contagious. blast your music. yes, you are gorgeous. get butterflies in your stomach when you see that special someone. some people are just dramatic. sometimes you think you know a person until one day you realize you don't really know them at all. you're never fully dressed without a smile.

event,"ok well ill first tell yall bout last night.. (sorry i didnt write.. i got home late n was dead tired.)
